                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/1079</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Assistant Chief of the Division of Far
                        Eastern Affairs</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>) <hi rend="italic">of
                        a Conversation With Captain Roscoe E. Schuirmann of the Office of Naval
                        Operations</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-07">December 7,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Captain Schuirmann telephoned Mr. Atcheson at ten minutes of five this evening
                    and stated that a report had been received from the British Admiralty that from
                    three to five Japanese ships were attacking Kota Bharu in British Malaya (just
                    below Siam, 6° north, 102° east) and attempting to land troops there. [(]This
                    information was communicated by Mr. Atcheson to the Secretary’s and to Mr.
                    Hornbeck’s office).</p>
            </div>
